Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with the problem of joint multiuser downlink beamforming and admission control in Cloud-RANs, which involves optimizing the transmission of information over a wireless network. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper focuses on the design of a green Cloud-RAN with limited fronthaul capacity, which involves networking and internet architecture aspects. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a bound improving Branch and Bound algorithm to solve the mixed integer nonlinear problem, which involves systems and control theory. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper considers the Quality of Service requirements of the MUs and proposes a polynomial-time heuristic algorithm to derive the sub-optimal solution, which involves artificial intelligence techniques. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a solution to the problem of joint multiuser downlink beamforming and admission control, which involves optimizing the network power consumption, and this can be seen as a machine learning problem.
